    "plan_cost_usd": 0.7996809,
    "plan_content": "Here's the complete implementation plan for the `Stepper` compound component:\n\n---\n\n## Architecture Decision\n\nThe `Stepper` follows the **`carousel.tsx` pattern** — React Context for state sharing, since `StepperTrigger`, `StepperSeparator`, and `StepperContent` all need to know about `activeStep` and `orientation` without prop drilling.\n\nTwo contexts are needed:\n- **`StepperContext`** (root-level): `activeStep` + `orientation`\n- **`StepperItemContext`** (per-step): `step` + derived `state` (`\"completed\" | \"active\" | \"pending\"`)\n\n---\n\n## 4 Changes Required\n\n### New file: `ui/stepper.tsx`\n7 named exports using function declarations. `StepperSeparator` reads **both** contexts (orientation from root, fill-state from item context), which means it lives **inside** `<StepperItem>` as a child — this is confirmed by the demo requirement (\"each step has a StepperTrigger, StepperTitle, and StepperSeparator\"). The separator fills (`bg-primary`) when the parent item's state is `\"completed\"`, i.e., when the user advances past that step.\n\n### New file: `examples/stepper-demo.tsx`\n3-step horizontal stepper with `React.useState(1)` for `activeStep`, clickable triggers, swappable content panels, and disabled-bounded Prev/Next buttons. Uses `export default` (as all example files do).\n\n### Modify `ui/_registry.ts`\nInsert `stepper` entry (no `dependencies` — pure React) between `spinner` (line 563) and `switch` (line 564), maintaining alphabetical order.\n\n### Modify `examples/_registry.ts`\nInsert `stepper-demo` entry with `registryDependencies: [\"stepper\"]` between `spinner-item` (line 2124) and `switch-demo` (line 2125).\n\nThe plan file at `/Users/timpietrusky/.claude/plans/merry-bubbling-gem.md` contains the complete, ready-to-paste code for all four changes.",
